On Thu, 29 Jun 2006, Robt Mann wrote:

> 	Thanx fellas for the useful warnings about various fuel pumps.
> 	But may I, from a motorcyclist perspective, point out that
> there's no obvious need for any fuel pump at all on a T2?


It's possible, at least if you keep the tank over 1/2 full!

The pump maintains a positive flow at all attitudes.  If you park the bus
nose-down with a near-empty tank gravity may not do the job.  Also,
gravity may not be sufficient to flow sufficient fuel at all times.

George
